result.execSummary:
The defendant David F. Eddy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

If the defendant is placed on probation or released to extended supervision, IT IS ORDERED that the defendant pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle on the highways until properly licensed.  Agent to work with defendant to obtain a valid driver's license.  

If defendant obtains a driver's license and agent recommends, he may apply for early discharge from probation.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.

Court advised defendant of the DNA submission requirement.

ADA Melissa Inlow appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Terrien.  Defendant plead to 2 Counts of  OAR and 2 counts of BJ.  Defendant plead no contest to counts 1 and 2 in 16CM91 and 16CM117.  Count 3 in 16CM117 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.  No authorization for disposal of the traffic citation. Court dismissed the traffic citation on it's own motion.   Court recited the charge and possible penalties on the counts he plead to.  Defendant understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of OAR, contrary to 343.44(1)(b), X2. and misdemeanor bail jumping contrary to 946.49(1)(a), X2.  State recommended 18 months probation.    Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle on the highways until properly licensed.   Agent to work with the defendant to obtain a valid driver's license.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  obtain and maintain employment.  Defendant does not want probation.  Requesting a fine, or 6 months probation.  If probation or jail, he will accept probation.  Court ordered:  sentence withheld, 18 months  probation.
